The National Union of Public Service and Allied Workers plans to shut down a DisChem warehouse following multiple positive COVID-19 cases.  JOHANNESBURG - The National Union of Public Service and Allied Workers (NUPSAW) plans to shut down a Dis-Chem warehouse following multiple positive COVID-19 cases. The union says there's been 10 positive COVID-19 cases, across several departments and claims the company has not carried out adequate screening and tracing processes. However, Dis-Chem says it has adhered to all requirements throughout the lockdown period. It says eight other positive cases were discovered during testing. READ: Employees can now check UIF COVID-19 relief benefit status "It started with one person being tested positive, the warehouse was closed and sanitised,” said Dis-Chem CEO, Ivan Saltzman. “The people and the area around the positive person was sanitised.” Saltzman says Dis-Chem tested 58 people and they were all in quarantine before the results were released.  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.